HEADWORD: Stupefaction
<hw>Stu`pe*fac"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>stup⟦eacute⟧faction</ets>. See <er>Stupefacient</er>.]</ety>
<def>The act of stupefying, or the state of being stupefied.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>stupifaction</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Resistance of the dictates of conscience brings a hardness and
<qex>stupefaction</qex> upon it.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stupefactive</ent>⟦br⟧
